<node CREATED="1527091053133" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1204019504" MODIFIED="1530117216251" TEXT="Comparable vs Comparator">
<richcontent TYPE="NOTE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p style="padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; line-height: 1.71429; vertical-align: baseline; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-style: none; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-right: 0px; font-size: 15px !important; margin-left: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin-top: 0px; border-left-style: none; border-top-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-right-style: none; border-top-style: none; text-align: justify; padding-bottom: 0px">
      <em style="border-right-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; padding-top: 0px; border-top-style: none; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); padding-right: 0px; text-transform: none; font-size: 13px; border-top-width: 0px; font-family: Open Sans, Helvetica, Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-bottom: 0px; border-right-style: none; border-bottom-width: 0px; text-indent: 0px; font-weight: 400; padding-left: 0px; border-bottom-style: none; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; border-left-style: none; padding-bottom: 0px; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0px; letter-spacing: normal" charset="utf-8"><font color="rgb(0, 0, 0)" size="15px" face="Open Sans, Helvetica, Arial, Verdana, sans-serif"><strong style="border-right-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; padding-top: 0px; border-top-style: none; padding-right: 0px; font-size: 15px; border-top-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; margin-bottom: 0px; border-right-style: none; border-bottom-width: 0px; padding-left: 0px; border-bottom-style: none; margin-right: 0px; border-left-style: none; margin-left: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; margin-top: 0px">If sorting of objects needs to be based on natural order then use Comparable </strong></font></em><font size="1"><br size="1" /></font><em style="border-right-width: 0px; padding-top: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border-top-style: none; padding-right: 0px; font-size: 13px; text-transform: none; border-top-width: 0px; font-family: Open Sans, Helvetica, Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: normal; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); word-spacing: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; text-indent: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-right-style: none; font-weight: 400; padding-left: 0px; border-bottom-style: none; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; border-left-style: none; padding-bottom: 0px; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0px; letter-spacing: normal" charset="utf-8"><font color="rgb(0, 0, 0)" size="15px" face="Open Sans, Helvetica, Arial, Verdana, sans-serif"><strong style="border-right-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; padding-top: 0px; border-top-style: none; padding-right: 0px; font-size: 15px; border-top-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; margin-bottom: 0px; border-right-style: none; border-bottom-width: 0px; padding-left: 0px; border-bottom-style: none; margin-right: 0px; border-left-style: none; margin-left: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; margin-top: 0px">whereas if you sorting needs to be done on attributes of different objects, then use Comparator in Java.</strong></font></em>
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
